\section*{Discrete mathematics: aka counting}

Lovely discussion of bean counting in Feynman's book on QED.  He will
describe how to set up the stories, and describe the beans.  How you
count them is now what makes it a hard math problem.  A worth while
read for winter break. (for undergrads--you grads have to get
down and write your papers over the summer.)

Why do we care?  Many situations have equally likelily probabilities:
\begin{itemize}
\item QM (hence Feynman's quote)
\item balls in urns
\item randomized controlled experiments
\item gambling
\item basic probability classes
\end{itemize}

